# 3) Compare the two runs (SOM-DIFF)

| **Kill-shot / Weakness** | **Pro Se Sev.** | **Lawyered Sev.** | **Delta** | **Fastest Patch** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Eleventh Amendment bar on damages | R | A | ↓ | Switch to Ex parte Young; move damages to individual-capacity claim |
| Younger abstention (no facts for bad-faith) | R | R | — | Add concrete bad-faith facts + cite Cullen/Schlagler |
| TRO: no bond mention | A | G | ↑ | Add bond line ("bond not required / nominal $100") |
- **Rule:** any Red that appears in either column = No-Go until patched.
- **Merge both Fix Lists** → re-run only the lenses you touched (Retest).

# 4) Quick prompts (copy/paste)

## Gemini – Cold, independent pass (run twice: once per draft)

<aside>
You are a neutral red-team reviewer. Do a cold read of the attached filing (no prior context). Run the 11-lens gauntlet (12(b)(6), jurisdiction/justiciability, abstention, immunities, TRO/PI, procedure, evidence, remedies, clerk gatekeeping, appellate preview, plain-English). Return JSON strictly matching this schema: {doc_id, mode, lenses_run, findings[], scores{likelihood_success, procedural_compliance, readability}}. For each finding give id, lens, claim, location, severity (R/A/G), what, why, patch, and 1–2 case_hooks. Be concise and concrete.

</aside>

## Gemini – Diff/Synthesis pass

<aside>
Given two JSON outputs (pro_se and lawyered) from the same schema, produce a SOM-DIFF table: show shared Reds, upgraded/downgraded items, and the 5 fastest patches that flip outcome likelihood. End with a Go/No-Go and a 150-word "Synthesis Judge" note.

</aside>

# 5) Go/No-Go gates

- **No-Go if:** any Red remains, TRO/PI compliance < 1.0, or clerk-bounce risks are unresolved.
- **Go when:** Reds cleared, key exhibits pinned, remedies tailored, and the one-page "Why We Win Now" is crisp.